reviews.text: I'm a non-Chinese local and they treated me very poorly. Black pepper beef was 90% onion and about five beef pieces. Stewed bamboo fungus was all lettuce and wood ear and no bamboo fungus at all. Deep fried eggplant with salty egg sauce was okay, but it was the biggest dish we received - and it was an appetizer. Very ordinary food and they only look after the regular customers. If you're a tourist, or even not Chinese: stay well away.

Good restsurant.
Good food.
Fairly friendly staff but I was there at a very busy period, so they were understandably under the pump. Kudos for their grace under pressure.

Lack of staff before the end of chinese new year. Long wait for tea refill and chasing dishes.
The food was actually not bad. Quantity was fine too.
Nice place for yum cha. Dim sum is great!

Food quality has dropped significantly compared to previous visits.

Came here for yum cha brunch, overall dim sum dishes lacked refinement, one of the  dishes, spring roll wrapped with cheong fun, was cold on the inside. Requested to return to the kitchen and the second plate was lukewarm. Lao sar pau did not 'lao'. Dumpling skins were thick and chewy.

The saving grace was the char siew and saliva chicken - still as good as before.

Feels like they changed their dim sum chef, it would explain why the brunch crowd has thinned.
